            },
            "answer_text": "I DO control that. Writers control everything about their book because they create it, word by word. Readers can certainly interpret it, but how I write the characters are the words the reader sees. What I don\u2019t control is how the reader thinks and feels about what I\u2019ve written. Once they\u2019ve read it, in a real sense it belongs to them. It becomes part of their experience. ",
